records.addlTxt:
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs including $360.00 to Metro Drug Unit;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) AODA assessment and follow through. (The Court will accept the assessment already completed by Ms. Lawrenz);
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Defendant is to use one doctor to prescribe medication and one pharmacist to fill those medications unless otherwise approved by the agent;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety;
7) Provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately;
9) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
10) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination.
The defendant has credit for 1 day if revoked.
Minutes.
